 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/udirrabey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dirra Bey</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Chanter's Pet</span><br>  Posts: 787<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/25/02 11:14:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=918.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Hey, if you have a firm that employs 90k peeps and less than 20% of management is female, they are obviously in violation of the civil rights acts -- there's no way that that few females are qualified for management positions. <br>
<br>
I never said that there shouldn't be equity -- there just shouldn't be quotas.<br>
<br>
It is entirely possible in a firm that there are not enough qualified candidates from a particular protected class that qualify to fill the positions in the proportion that their population is present in the general population -- ie, it's entirely possible that microsoft couldn't find enough black C++ programmers qualified to fill 10% of their programming positions, even tho blacks make up 10% of the population in seattle. My argument is that MS shouldn't be forced to hire 10% of their programmers from black people just because there are 10% blacks in the population. Instead, let's make sure that everyone has the opportunity to learn the skills necessary, and the market will take care of the rest.<br>
<br>
The idea that there are less than 20% of women qualified for management when the population of women is over 50% is silly; your firm is obviously discriminating. And is open to massive lawsuits. But that really has nothing to do with quotas. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uismaeldf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IsmaelDF</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pig<font color=#FF0000>?</font> Pig<font color=#FF0000>?</font></span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/26/02 12:36:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=918.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Well, I've seen how well Affirmative Action works first-hand.<br>
<br>
My father applied for a job with the state government, along with two other white guys and a black guy.  He was told after the interview process that they needed to hire the black guy to fill their quota.  My father was the most qualified, but he isn't black, so the black guy got the job.  Tell me this is just one isolated case where Affirmative Action didn't work out the way you people say it does, and I'll be more than happy to dig up a dozen more stories of the same.  <br>
<br>
 <p>Ismael Mindreaver<br>
