<br>
Affirmative Action was not about quota's  read <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.aclu.org/community/calif-n/myth.html">www.aclu.org/community/calif-n/myth.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> . It was about reaching further to ensure your hiring practices did not violate civil rights.<br>
<br>
It is easy to get sucked up in to your individual experience and state &quot;that is the impact&quot; but the mere fact that I work for an organization that has a desire to hire 20% women by 2010 in sr. mgt  goes to show the world still has a long way to go.  This was in their shareholder report, this is an acceptable practice today. That means that today there are less then 20% women and mind you they never mentioned black or hispanic individuals in that percentage. <br>
<br>
The notion that the market controls itself is totally unrealistic. Go to yahoo and type Nigeria or Indonesia and oil companies and see how humane corporations are. <br>
<br>
There is nothing that makes me sadder then to see a woman in here advocating on these topics, get out of college and spend five years in a highly successful organization and tell me what you think then. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/utewlbocks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tewlbocks</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Master</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/26/02 4:00:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=918.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ...</span><hr size=1> This does raise an interesting question:  Does affirmative action propagate discrimination?  Will the more qualified guy that didn't get the job subconscientiously (or maybe conscientiously) harbor resentment for the minority that did?  It probably happens if the candidate finds out why he/she wasn't hired. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/utatianaefatecaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatianae Fatecaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><HR><font color=#660066><CENTER>Drinal Ally<BR>******</CENTER></font><HR></span><br>  Posts: 840<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/26/02 4:06:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=918.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  ...</span><hr size=1> Quote<br>
<br>
Even where there is evidence of discrimination, affirmative action plans are only permitted by the courts if they: <br>
<br>
* avoid using quotas;<br>
* are flexible;<br>
* do not require the selection of unqualified candidates;<br>
* are designed to last no longer than necessary to remedy the discrimination; and<br>
* do not displace incumbent white male employees or businesses. <br>
<br>
